---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
import DiffTool from '../components/DiffTool.tsx';
import LandingLinks from '../components/LandingLinks.astro';
---

<ToolPage
  title="Text Diff Checker — Compare Two Texts Online"
  description="Compare two texts online for free. Paste an original and a changed version to highlight every added, removed and modified line, with word-level changes. Runs in your browser."
  h1="Text Diff Checker"
  intro="Paste an original text on the left and the changed version on the right to see exactly what was added, removed or modified — line by line, down to the individual word. Switch between split and unified views, and share a link to your comparison. Everything stays in your browser."
  path="/diff"
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'Is my text uploaded anywhere?',
      a: 'No. The comparison runs entirely in your browser — nothing you paste is sent to a server unless you choose to create a shareable link.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can I see word-level changes, not just whole lines?',
      a: 'Yes. When a line is modified rather than fully added or removed, the specific words that changed are highlighted within the line.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How does the shareable link work?',
      a: 'The Copy shareable link button encodes both texts into the URL itself, so opening that link restores the same comparison. The data lives in the link, not on our servers.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Should I share sensitive text with the link feature?',
      a: 'No. A shareable link contains the compared text in the URL. Anyone who receives or records that URL may be able to read it, so do not use it for secrets or private documents.',
    },
  ]}
>
  <DiffTool client:only="react" />

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">What is a diff checker?</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      A diff checker compares two pieces of text and shows precisely how they differ — which lines
      were added, which were removed, and which were changed. It is indispensable for reviewing edits
      to code, contracts, configuration files, articles or any text where a small change matters.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How to use it</h2>
    <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Paste the original text into the left panel and the changed text into the right.</li>
      <li>Added lines are highlighted in green, removed lines in red, with changed words marked inline.</li>
      <li>Toggle <strong>Ignore case</strong> or <strong>Ignore whitespace</strong> to focus on meaningful changes.</li>
      <li>Switch between <strong>Split</strong> and <strong>Unified</strong> views, or copy a shareable link.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Choose the right comparison view</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Split view keeps old and new text side by side, which is useful when line order stays mostly
      stable. Unified view puts additions and removals into one stream, making it easier to review on
      a narrow screen. Word-level highlighting explains small edits inside a changed line instead of
      marking the entire sentence as unrelated.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">When to ignore case or whitespace</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Ignore whitespace when indentation or line padding changed but content did not. Ignore case for
      prose or identifiers only when capitalization is genuinely irrelevant. For source code, JSON
      keys, passwords and case-sensitive configuration, leave case comparison enabled so meaningful
      changes are not hidden.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Privacy and shareable links</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Normal comparisons happen locally in your browser. The optional shareable link is different:
      it encodes both texts into the URL so another browser can reconstruct the comparison without a
      database. Treat that URL as containing the original documents. Do not create or send one for
      credentials, private contracts, personal data or proprietary source code.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Is my text uploaded anywhere?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      No. The comparison runs entirely in your browser — nothing you paste is sent to a server unless
      you choose to create a shareable link.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Can I see word-level changes, not just whole lines?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      Yes. When a line is modified rather than fully added or removed, the specific words that changed
      are highlighted within the line.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">How does the shareable link work?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      The Copy shareable link button encodes both texts into the URL itself, so opening that link
      restores the same comparison. The data lives in the link, not on our servers.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Should I share sensitive text with the link feature?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      No. A shareable link contains the compared text in the URL. Anyone who receives or records that
      URL may be able to read it, so do not use it for secrets or private documents.
    </p>

    <LandingLinks group="diff" heading="More comparison tools" />
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>
